    processed_data = loader.handle(test_data)

    # Assertions to check each stage
    assert "raw_data" in processed_data
    assert "clean_data" in processed_data
    assert "transformed_data" in processed_data
    assert "stored_data" in processed_data
    print("All stages passed successfully")

# Main function demonstrating use (inactive due to testing)
if __name__ == "__main__":
    pytest.main()
```
This code provides a clean, modular approach utilizing the Chain of Responsibility pattern along with pytest for validation of each step in the processing pipeline. Each handler processes the information and passes it along to the next, ensuring separation of concerns and easier maintenance.

